cho_description:
Upper portion of a granodiorite standing statue of the goddess Sekhmet, the face broken around the mouth and the solar-disk headdress partly missing. Wears a wig and a close-fitting dress, decorated with rosettes on the shoulder straps. Left arm broken off and missing; right arm survives only in upper section near the shoulder.

EA599 

COL: http://www.britishmuseum.org/research/collection_online/collection_object_details.aspx?partId=1&objectId=1340547

Created from 179 photographs by Jennifer Wexler
